# AlignEd Doctrine

Copyright (c) 2026 EdTech. All rights reserved.

AlignEd is an anonymous, web-based career-guidance platform for Philippine
Senior High School students: a strict four-step journey (Landing → Profile
Setup → RIASEC Assessment → Results Dashboard) with strand validation, career
and degree-program suggestions, PDF export, and email delivery.
`docs/AlignEd_PRD.md` is the single source of truth — any feature outside the
four-step journey requires explicit approval before a line of code is written.

Stack is fixed: Next.js 16.2.5 App Router (breaking changes vs Next 15 — read
`docs/Next16_Delta_Notes.md` and the bundled docs at
`node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before framework work), React 19, TypeScript
(strict), Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui on Base UI, vendored MagicUI/Aceternity/Efferd
components, framer-motion 12 (`motion/react`), Supabase (Postgres, RLS, Edge
Functions — the Auth product is deliberately unused), Resend for email.

## Hard rules
- Never introduce user accounts, authentication, or persistence of personally
  identifiable information. AlignEd is anonymous by design (PRD §3 Non-Goals).
- Never introduce conflicting third-party services without explicit approval.
- Production-ready only: strict types, zod validation, error handling, tests.
- Prioritize security, privacy (Data Privacy Act of 2012), and low-end mobile
  performance in every decision.
- When uncertain, pick the simplest safe default and state the tradeoff.
- Include the copyright line above in file headers, READMEs, and docs.

## For every non-trivial deliverable, cover
Summary, Why (tied to a PRD requirement ID), Design (structure), DB changes
(SQL migration, if any), API/Edge Function (handler + examples), Frontend
(component + usage), Tests (unit + e2e), Deployment notes (env vars),
Acceptance criteria (mapped to PRD §9).

## Process
- Review existing files before refactor. Make a todo list and run major
  changes by the user first. Keep changes atomic and reviewable.
- Do not auto-commit; do not auto-push. Do not auto-commit docs/activity logs.
